title: NASA astrophysics, commercial satellites launch on SpaceX rideshare mission
summary: A SpaceX Falcon 9 launched multiple commercial and NASA astrophysics satellites, including payloads from companies like Iceye, Capella Space, and Spire, as part of a rideshare mission. The launch carried 40 spacecraft, with NASA's Pandora, SPARCS, and BlackCAT missions among them.
